[2] Skunk, canine - North Carolina
Date: 27 Oct 2010
Source: Daily Tar Heel [edited]
<http://www.dailytarheel.com/index.php/article/2010/10/orange_county_finds_sixth_positive_rabies_test_this_year>


Orange County Animal Services received its 6th positive rabies test
result Wednesday [27 Oct 2010]. A skunk was tested after it was found
to have potential exposure with a dog at an Orange County residence
near High Rock Road and Maple Avenue in Efland.

On 26 Oct 2010, a resident woke early to her outdoor dog barking, and
saw the skunk run under her porch, when she brought her dog inside and
called the animal control.

Though the resident did not have direct contact with the skunk, she
did have direct contact with her dog, who was vaccinated against
rabies. A Communicable Disease Nurse from Orange County's Health
Department will contact the residents involved to evaluate their risk
of rabies exposure.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

