[3] Canine - North Carolina
Date: 2 Nov 2010
Source: WECT.com [edited]
<http://www.wect.com/Global/story.asp?S=13430110>


The number of rabies cases have increased to 9 in New Hanover County
this year [2010], with a positive test on a case involving a dog on
Holland Drive. The incident happened Monday [1 Nov 2010].

Animals with a current rabies vaccination when they're bit need to be
re-boostered within 5 days. The Centers for Disease Control also
recommends that unvaccinated pets be put down. Rabies can be
transmitted by a bite, salivary contact to an open wound, and salivary
contact to mucous membranes.

Animals with suspected cases of rabies should be handled with
protective gloves. The same goes for personal pets exposed to rabies.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

