[5] Bat, human exposure - Texas
Date 27 Oct 2010
Source: HCN On Line [edited]
<http://www.hcnonline.com/articles/2010/10/27/atascocita_observer/news/44rabidbat.txt>


A young boy, around 8 years old, is undergoing a series of rabies
shots after he found a dead bat at the Lindsay Lyons sports complex in
Atascocita on 19 Oct 2010, Humble Baseball Association (HBA) officials
say. The Harris County Precinct 4 Commissioner's Office confirmed the
bat tested positive for rabies.

HBA treasurer Sarah Wooley, who also serves as area director for
Nation's Baseball, HBA's national affiliate, said the boy has received
3 rabies shots.

Wooley said a group of kids were playing on an unoccupied baseball
field while games were in progress on other nearby fields when one of
the children found a dead bat that was apparently only recently
deceased just outside the fence-line.

The parents of the boy who was the primary handler of the bat were
close-by, Wooley said, watching an older brother play ball. The boy's
parents were informed, and Harris County Public Health and
Environmental Services officials were called. One of the boys' mother
requested the bat be tested for rabies.

According to county records, the parents of the affected child were
notified of the positive test results on 22 Oct 2010. The HBA has
since sent out notices to all parents, and county officials have
posted notices around the sports complex informing visitors of the
recent developments.

[Byline: Stefanie Thomas]

