[8] Raccoon, canine - Connecticut
Date: 2 Nov 2010
Source: The Day.com [edited]
<http://www.theday.com/article/20101102/NWS01/311029927/-1/nws>


A raccoon found near Warwick Terrace has tested positive for rabies,
Ledge Light Health District said Monday (1 Nov 2010).

The raccoon came into a resident's yard on Saturday [30 Oct 2010]. The
homeowner's 2 dogs were in the yard at the time, and one of the dogs
bit the raccoon, said George Calkins, senior sanitarian at Ledge
Light. One of the dogs was up-to-date on its rabies vaccine, but the
other had been overdue for a vaccine for a few days so must be
quarantined for 2 weeks, Calkins said. The raccoon was caught by the
town's animal control officer and taken to the state laboratory for
rabies testing.

Calkins said that although there was no human contact with the
raccoon, the owner is being checked by a physician as a precaution.
Signs warning about the rabid raccoon will be posted in the
neighborhood, located off Vauxhall Street Extension and Greentree Drive.

The public is reminded to refrain from feeding or approaching any wild
animals. For information, call the health district or the animal
control officer.

--
